# ex

> Command-line text editor
> See also: vim
> More information: https://www.vim.org

- Open a file:

`ex {file something}`

- Save and Quit:

`wq<Enter>`

- Undo the last operation:

`undo<Enter>`

- Search for a pattern in the file:

`/{any something}<Enter>`

- Perform a regular expression substitution in the whole file:

`%s/{any something}/{any something}/g<Enter>`

- Insert text:

`i<Enter>{any something}<C-c>`

- Switch to Vim:

`visual<Enter>`
